<img loading="lazy" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1989430 lazyload" src="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/NNPP-Ajadi-Kwankwaso-Ibadan.png" alt="" width="919" height="503" srcset="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/NNPP-Ajadi-Kwankwaso-Ibadan.png 919w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/NNPP-Ajadi-Kwankwaso-Ibadan-320x175.jpg 320w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/NNPP-Ajadi-Kwankwaso-Ibadan-640x350.jpg 640w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/NNPP-Ajadi-Kwankwaso-Ibadan-600x328.jpg 600w" sizes="(max-width: 919px) 100vw, 919px" /> The New Nigeria People’s Party (NNPP) presidential candidate, Dr. Rabiu Musa Kwankwaso, made headlines in Ibadan on Thursday as he formally presented the party’s flag to several party members, including Ambassador Olufemi Ajadi Oguntoyinbo, the Ogun governorship candidate of the party; Olukayode Joshua Popoola, the Oyo governorship candidate, and Otunba Jim-Kamal for Lagos. The presentation took place at the Southwest rally of the party held at the Liberty Stadium, Ibadan, where thousands of the party’s supporters came out to show their support. The event was a testament to the NNPP’s increasing popularity and momentum in the region, as the party demonstrated its commitment to taking the mantle of leadership. With a large number of supporters, the NNPP has shown that it is a force to be reckoned with, and the public’s interest in the party is growing. The rally was an unforgettable experience for those in attendance, with thousands of NNPP supporters coming together to show their support for the party and its vision for Nigeria. The NNPP’s platform emphasizes the importance of good governance, social justice, and economic empowerment, and the party has shown that it is not afraid to take on the challenges facing Nigeria. With a highly experienced team of leaders, the NNPP is poised to make a significant impact in the region and beyond, as it continues to work towards a better future for Nigeria and its people. The event at Liberty Stadium was a key milestone for the NNPP, and its supporters left the rally feeling inspired and motivated to continue the fight for a better Nigeria. The NNPP’s commitment to the cause, coupled with the unwavering support of its supporters, makes the party a force to be reckoned with in the upcoming elections. 